People describing themselves as wild barbarians always comes as more honest from sedentary intellectuals and produces a striking effect, IIRC Walt Whitmann also wrote some of his best poetry about nature and wilderness while stuck at a clerky indoor office job, not a coincidence.

One thing I am very passionate about in video games is seasonal maps. E.g. if you play Counter-Strike in December there should be snow on the ground in de_dust2. I remember back in the day at least on League they did a snowy Summoner's Rift for Christmas... What a wonderful idea.

Ideally there should also be a day/night cycle based on server time where you get to play the daytime version of the map from morning until the late afternoon with an evening and nighttime versions later on. Helps get you in the mood and makes it feel less trance-like.

Increasing the average lifespan by just like ~20 years sounds less ridiculous and would mean everyone gets to meet their great grandparents, like 8 extra close relatives you get to love and learn from... Something that would totally change family dynamics and general culture imo.
